##ANTI-DOMESTIC VIOLENCE VOLUNTEERS IN 23 cities call for your help

Micro signal

Features an introduction to the refreshing flavor of the feminist hardcore

On March 4, The sun was shining brightly in Jinan, and there were bare tree shadows on the red brick walls. There was also an anti domestic violence proposal with a handwritten women's Federation and police phone number on it, and a drawing of a love heart. A woman in a long red coat and white gloves stopped to take a closer look. This is the braised pork paste after the proposal to see, she will take this scene.

Two days ago, braised pork in the micro blog to see students Xiao Ling print a "to the neighbors of the anti-domestic Violence Proposal" (hereinafter referred to as "the proposal") posted in the district elevator door. Braised pork replied that he would join in.

Braised pork in brown sauce and little Rin went online on March 1 as a "mini-vaccine against domestic violence" (mini-vaccine) . It calls on people to care for their communities and to intervene in domestic violence around them.

You can become an anti-domestic violence vaccine on the Internet and share your actions; in reality, you can print or hand-write the proposal and post it in a prominent place in your community.

Many people are impressed by the following data:

24.7 per cent of the country's 270 million households have experienced some form of domestic violence;
An average of one woman is beaten by her husband every 7.4 seconds;
The average victim has suffered 35 domestic assaults before calling 911.

This is a statistic from the all-china Women's Federation, which reflects the seriousness and prevalence of domestic violence.

New Crown Pneumonia outbreak so far, the majority of people in the country as a unit to gather, isolation, work, housework, child-rearing contradictions concentrated presentation. In such a high-pressure situation, whether domestic violence will increase?

Beauty Blogger Yu ya tells of her experiences with domestic violence

Wanfei's story bears this out. Wan Fei is a police officer and head of the Blue Sky Women and Children Protection Association, an anti-domestic violence charity in Jianli County, Hubei Province. In his Sixth Tone article, he said that in February 2020, Jianli County police received 162 reports of domestic violence, three times as many as in the same period last year (47) ; the number of reports in January was twice as many as in the same period last year. And that's just the numbers from the reports.

The population of Jianli County is 1.566 million, the province of Hubei is 59.17 million and the national population is 1.4 billion, according to Baidu Baike. In February 2020, Hubei Province may have had 6,000 cases of domestic violence, and China may have had 140,000. The epidemic has isolated the victims of domestic violence as "isolated islands" , making it difficult for them to seek help and for external resources to intervene.

The anti-domestic violence vaccine is trying to set a course between islands, to send a message -- I'm here, I'm watching you.

Little Rin
I wiped the blood off myself and went to bed

Xiao Lin is the 941st minor vaccine and a victim of domestic violence.

At the beginning is the kindergarten fuzzy memory, after primary school, small Rin clearly remember his father to his mother's domestic violence, sometimes once a week, sometimes 2,3 days will quarrel once. Every time he did it, it was after his father had been drinking. My father had written several repenting letters, and in the end the promise of a repenting letter lapsed.

In the third grade, one of the most serious parental conflicts occurred. They quarreled and fought. Father pushed mother under the stairs going up and down the bed. Mother cried out to little Rin to call for help. But she was too scared to react. My father also took all my mother's clothes out of the closet and set them on fire in the bathroom. Little Rin thought the whole house was going to burn.

It wasn't just the House that burned down, it was the relationship between the parents. Mother went to court to sue father for divorce. The judge came out and asked Little Rin, do you want to go with your mother or your father? Little Rin didn't answer. Little Rin was given to her father to raise. Later, she learned that children under the age of 10 did not have the right to choose their parents when their parents divorced.

In fact, only the bathroom was blackened, and Xiao Lin and his father lived in the house for another three years. For the first two years, little Rin did not experience physical violence, but there will be psychological pressure.

In the 5th and 6th grades of Primary School, Xiao Lin was studying Zheng. One day, small Rin did not back the score down, her father took the score has been slapping her face. Her cheeks were swollen, and there was blood in her mouth. It was the first time her father had ever used physical violence against her without drinking. "then I wiped the blood off myself and went to bed. "

The next day was the weekend, and both he and his father pretended that nothing had happened. In addition to friends, small Rin did not tell his mother, the elderly, she did not know how to deal with, but also ashamed to say.

One night on the second day, my father took Xiao Lin to a friend's house for a drink. At one or two in the morning, they walked to the garden below their house. He made her sit by the side of the road and wouldn't let her come home. The father said a bunch of words, then took the mobile phone to small RIN's face.

A college student was passing by. He shouted from across the street, "you can't hit a child in the street. "

My father said angrily, "this is my family's business, what business is it of yours? "

College student: "If you do that again, I will call the police. "

He did call the police. He was standing across the road watching. "father is tall and strong, he may also be afraid. " Small Rin thanked the stranger very much, otherwise, that night do not know what will happen.

At two or three in the morning, when the police arrived, she felt a little relieved. Responding to the police, asking are male police, small Rin has been crying, both afraid and embarrassed, do not know what to say. Small Rin does not want to go home, she is afraid of the police to put his father back, to continue to get along. She spent the night in the women's quarters. She remembers the policewoman wiping the blood off her face and pouring her a glass of water.

At 7 or 8 the next morning, little rinn's mother came to the police station to pick her up. She was so impressed that when her mother handed in her papers, a male policeman looked them in the eye and said in a tone of disgust that he didn't want to do anything about it anymore. "He thinks we're trouble, " said Xiao, who has since had some trouble with the police.

After that, she lived with her mother. Parents Form New families. Mother and her partner occasionally quarrel. During the outbreak, Xiao Lin felt that the frequency of quarrels increased. Once, the 4-and-a-half-year-old sister shouted, "don't fight. " But they continued. Little Rin took her sister to another space and didn't want her to have that memory.

"Some words are spoken, and some deeds, once done, are like folded paper, always leaving a mark. "She wants her family to pay attention to the way they communicate and the language they use to avoid violence. She taped the proposal to the elevator door, though she did not tell her family that she had done it. "They should be able to see it when they go down. "

For Small Rin, the more voices, the domestic violence will be changed. She hoped that her future career in law, the media and the police would help women and vulnerable groups.

Robin
"It's hard to move, but it takes the edge off. "

Robin was a feminist who knew that the anti-domestic violence vaccine was recommended by her feminist partner. Robin printed out 20 proposals at once. She told her mom she was gonna put it up in the community. She and her mother were nervous about being seen, being caught on camera and being blamed by the property.

On March 3, Robin walked around the neighborhood with a small plastic bag before heading home. She repented and spent the night building herself up. "It's a good thing for the community. There's nothing to be afraid of. ".

The next day, she went out again. At first, Robin posted the proposal on a bulletin board at the door of each building. But the bulletin board is far away from the elevator buttons, so you probably won't see it. She noticed a leaflet in the elevator with the words "prevention of new crown pneumonia" and posted the proposal next to it.

In the process, an old couple got into the elevator. The grandfather asked, "sister, what are you pasting? "
The grandfather was not hostile, but Robin said sheepishly, "This is an anti-domestic violence initiative. "

Robin had never before seen "unofficial" people posting information of public interest, and she had never had the opportunity to support or advocate for something as an individual. Everyone is hidden behind associations, companies, and units. "There's a sense of being out of touch, " said Robin, who doesn't worry so much about putting up a commercial; she worries about legitimacy even if it's good for the community.

Robin noticed that there were various advertisements in the community, such as the card dealer, the teahouse, the photo studio, the foot wash... Robin thought the proposal had more legitimacy on the wall than those advertisements. Robin found practical action harder than understanding theory, "but it eliminates feelings of powerlessness. "

That night, Robin's mother came home from work and asked her, "are you done? Do you want me to come with you? " Robin was happy, even if she didn't know what feminism was, but she was just as good a feminist as she was.

Hey, remy
"A drop of ink will not darken the sea. "

Xiaomi, which is eight years old, is the youngest of the vaccines.

Millet mother told Millet about the "small vaccine" activities, asked her to go to paste posters. Without much explanation, Xiaomi agreed.

The following are three patterns, the first is Love "everyone love, Home Security" ; the second is "Domestic Violence" ; the third is a brush with a drop of ink into the sea, it says "a drop of ink can not make the sea black. Xiaomi explained that the sea is tolerant of others, and even if the ink drips in, the sea is still blue and will not turn black. "I hope all of us can be tolerant of others, do not easily go to hit others. "

Millet and rice put up four posters, one of which was posted on the express cabinet, because there are many people. Xiaomi has a trick. Every time we pass a poster, if someone follows us, Xiaomi will pretend to be a passer-by and look at it closely, hoping that others will also look at it.

At this point, millet showed the picture just painted, a corner of the mouth down the expression, right eye drooping a huge tear, she said it is sad mood, "because no one to see the poster. ". Millet evening and a few students video, she intends to let the students to spread the story of no domestic violence.

For Xiaomi, violence is inherently wrong.

Participants in the anti-domestic violence mini-vaccine

Why add the anti-domestic violence vaccine?

Some people are able to understand and empathize with others because of their own experiences; some people are happy because they help others; some people are angry because of violence; some people think mistakes need to be corrected; some people think this is an exercise, to Grow Up. Everyone has their own answer.

As of 12 o'clock on March 7, "anti-domestic Violence Small Vaccine" launch for seven days, thousands of people to join the "anti-domestic violence small vaccine. More than 50 participants posted the "anti-domestic violence initiative for neighbors" in communities in 23 cities, including Beijing, Guangzhou, Shenzhen, Wuhan, Dalian, Panzhihua and Luoyang.

We hope that more than 10,000 people will join the anti-domestic violence vaccine. If you are willing to be one in 10,000, please scan the Qr code below to join.

What do anti-domestic violence vaccines do

1. Tweet your name and Tag it: Anti domestic violence in the middle of the epidemic.
Print or hand-copy the anti-domestic violence initiative for your neighborhood and post it in your neighborhood hallway, elevator, or anywhere else that stands out. After posting, (1) you can take a picture of it and post it on your Weibo with Tag: anti-domestic violence during the epidemic; (2) you can submit it to Weibo@tianai eliminate domestic violence BOT.
3. If you have domestic violence happening around you, or have any questions about domestic violence, please feel free to post to@tiantianai eliminate domestic violence BOT.

Robin

"It's hard to move, but it takes the edge off. "

Robin was a feminist who knew that the anti-domestic violence vaccine was recommended by her feminist partner. Robin printed out 20 proposals at once. She told her mom she was gonna put it up in the community. She and her mother were nervous about being seen, being caught on camera and being blamed by the property.

On March 3, Robin walked around the neighborhood with a small plastic bag before heading home. She repented and spent the night building herself up. "It's a good thing for the community. There's nothing to be afraid of. ".

The next day, she went out again. At first, Robin posted the proposal on a bulletin board at the door of each building. But the bulletin board is far away from the elevator buttons, so you probably won't see it. She noticed a leaflet in the elevator with the words "prevention of new crown pneumonia" and posted the proposal next to it.

In the process, an old couple got into the elevator. The grandfather asked, "sister, what are you pasting? "
The grandfather was not hostile, but Robin said sheepishly, "This is an anti-domestic violence initiative. "

Robin had never before seen "unofficial" people posting information of public interest, and she had never had the opportunity to support or advocate for something as an individual. Everyone is hidden behind associations, companies, and units. "There's a sense of being out of touch, " said Robin, who doesn't worry so much about putting up a commercial; she worries about legitimacy even if it's good for the community.

Robin noticed that there were various advertisements in the community, such as the card dealer, the teahouse, the photo studio, the foot wash... Robin thought the proposal had more legitimacy on the wall than those advertisements. Robin found practical action harder than understanding theory, "but it eliminates feelings of powerlessness. "

That night, Robin's mother came home from work and asked her, "are you done? Do you want me to come with you? " Robin was happy, even if she didn't know what feminism was, but she was just as good a feminist as she was.
